Job description

Australia Post is changing at an incredible pace. In the Business and Government department, we’ve integrated technological services that help large organisations and government departments adapt in an increasingly digital world without relegating on our historically successful offering of parcels and mail - all of which helps move Australia forward.


And we’re only getting started.


Nowadays, our plans are to lead the enterprise, business and government service space by encompassing our full range of products. And to get there, we’re on the lookout for ambitious people to join our truly diverse team. Working within a start-up culture that’s backed by all the resources Australia Post provides, the opportunity to innovate and push boundaries to improve services for all Australians is ready and waiting.


What it's like to work here:


For you, it means you'll do great work, learn from the best and develop a career within a robust and well-invested but empowering and creative environment. We all work hard – we're working on major challenges, after all – but we also recognise that you have a life outside of the office, so we provide flexible conditions that enable you to grow whilst enjoying genuine work life balance.


What does the role involve?


This role is responsible for defining and delivering on the Marketing strategy for their segments, through the Sales enablement, Customer engagement and Enterprise marketing functions. The role’s core purpose is to partner with the segment development teams to ensure our segment development activity is underpinned by a thorough understanding of the market and competitor landscape and will translate effectively into solutions to drive growth in the segments and sub-segments.

\xa0

The Senior Manager, Segment Marketing will be forward thinking and ensure that we know how to expand and grow our offerings as appropriate. They will use insights and analysis to determine the channel preferences for the team and articulate the strategy for when and how to market offerings

\xa0

Success in this role will be achieved by embedding a strategic marketing approach into our Segment development, defining the segment marketing strategy, aligned with the enterprise strategy and utilising the enterprise marketing Centre of Excellence to gather analytics and insights and deliver on campaigns as required.

\xa0

  • Drive strategic agenda and lead marketing activities for the Enterprise and Government segment to enhance the growth strategy and expand its existing business in line with financial targets.
  • Define and deliver the marketing strategy for the Segments, based on the Segment Strategy, segmentation and CVPs.
  • Liaise with the relationship manager within the enterprise marketing function to ensure the central services are best utilised to deliver on the segment’s needs
  • Partner with sales, product and solution engines to leverage existing capabilities (in identity, payments, retail and deliveries) and new investments to shape new offers and deliver them to market.
  • Work closely with the Segment Development teams to identify and clarify customer value propositions and work with customer experience teams to embed feedback and insights across sales and product development initiatives.
  • Partner with and guide the Sales Enablement, Industry Engagement and enterprise marketing function to deliver thought leadership, targeted customer/influencer engagement and integrated marketing communications programs to grow our sales pipeline and improve customer acquisition, retention and advocacy.
  • Support the development of deal strategies to win large scale enterprise and government services contracts in the provision of identity, payments and omni-channel services.
  • Drive an innovation agenda and lead key initiatives as required to identify and establish new strategic partnerships/ventures
  • Identify and refresh core customer value propositions, support development of integrated portfolio roadmaps (product, marketing, and channel) and build customer advocacy measures.
  • Through the demand generation and database marketing team, develop and implement brand positioning, demand generation and targeted customer/influencer engagement programs to grow sales pipeline and improve customer advocacy.
  • Lead key initiatives as required across (not exhaustive) marketing, product development, innovation/venturing, and cultural transformation programs in support of growth initiatives.
  • Demonstrate thought leadership and innovation that positions Australia Post as a digital transformation leader.
  • Drive an uplift in revenue and profit outcomes for B&G segment and Australia Post

\xa0

What experience will you have?


For this role we’re looking for someone who has:


  • Extensive experience in a strategic marketing/communications role within a commercial setting
  • Extensive experience in the provision of strategic advice and support in the context of large, complex organisation undergoing significant change
  • Experience in leveraging customer insights to contribute to the development of tailored, innovative and differentiated customer solutions
  • Strong attention to detail and the ability to effectively manage competing and changing priorities
  • Experience in proactively leading change by influencing others to stretch boundaries and overcome obstacles
  • High level of consultancy experience dealing with senior executives
  • Strong commercial acumen, creativity and initiative
  • Strong analytical and problem solving skills
  • Proven experience managing relationships with C-suite level stakeholders, customers and partners
  • Demonstrated experience building strong cross functional working relationships within a matrix environment
  • Experience driving initiatives that gain buy-in and sign off from senior stakeholder groups
  • Understanding of policies and practices applicable to areas within TeS
  • Understanding of Australia Post’s governance, regulatory and compliance requirements (e.g. Community Service Obligations) and the implications for the way we do business.
  • Knowledge of organisational dynamics and culture.
  • Understanding of Australia Post’s business drivers, strategy, and competitive advantage (e.g. Speed, service performance, value for money) and the impact on how Australia Post operates (what drives cost, supply, demand)


Benefits & Culture:


We believe a diverse and inclusive workplace brings out the best in our people. We encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities, cultures and disabilities. A career at Australia Post Group can lead down many paths and we are passionate about offering a supportive, inclusive culture, competitive compensation and flexible working conditions that enable you to develop whilst enjoying genuine work life balance.
